Objective¶

Given a Bank customer, build a neural network based classifier that can determine whether they will leave or not in the next 6 months.

Import Libraries¶

In [1]:

warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

Separate out independent and dependent variables¶

In [30]:
X = df.iloc[:,:10]
Y = df.iloc[:,10]

Get dummies for Categorical variables¶

In [31]:
New_Geography=pd.get_dummies(X['Geography'])
New_Gender=pd.get_dummies(X['Gender'])
In [32]:
X=pd.concat([X,New_Geography,New_Gender],axis=1)
X=X.drop(['Geography','Gender'],axis=1)

Normalize the data¶

In [33]:
X=preprocessing.normalize(X)

Divide into train and test¶

In [34]:
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, Y, test_size=0.30,random_state=1)   # Split data in 70:30 ratio

sc = StandardScaler()

Build the model¶

Activation function as 'elu'¶

In [40]:
model1 = Sequential()
# Add the first hidden layer
model1.add(Dense(64, input_shape = (13,), activation = 'elu'))
# Adding the second hidden layer
model1.add(Dense(32, activation = 'elu'))
# Adding the output layer
model1.add(Dense(1, activation = 'sigmoid'))
Learning rate as 0.001¶
In [41]:
sgd = optimizers.Adam(lr = 0.001)
Loss function binary cross entropy¶
In [42]:
model1.compile(optimizer = sgd, loss = 'binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

Conclusion¶

As we see above even after changing learning rate and/or activation functions we get different accuracies and loss.

However, out of all tried models and parameters, we get best results with "elu" as first layer activation function and "relu" as second hidden layer activation function with learning rate as 0.01. We have kept batch size and epochs consistent as 50 and 100 respectively.

  • Please note these can/would change on each run.
